{
  "texts": [
    "11 This research angle carries over to teaching as well since students are also expected to produce outputs that are the results of their own work.",
    "Furthermore, they also often do their own research (such as literature search and review) in support of their projects, homework, thesis, and other forms of performance evaluation.",
    "Accountability and responsibility in university first responses.",
    "The rapidly changing nature of the subject matter poses a significant challenge for scholars to assess the state of play of human responsibility.",
    "This is well exemplified by the reversal of hearts by some Australian universities (see Rudolph et al. (2023) quoting newspaper articles) who first disallowed the use of AI by students while doing assignments, just to reverse that decision a few months later and replace it by a requirement of disclosing the use of AI in homeworks."
  ]
}